casebody.data:
J. O’NEILL FAIRLEIGH AND JOSEPH MORTON, EXECUTORS OF THE LAST WILL AND TESTAMENT OF WILLIAM HIGGINS, DECEASED, PROSECUTORS, v. NEWTON A. K. BUGBEE, COMPTROLLER OF THE TREASURY OF THE STATE OF NEW JERSEY, DEFENDANT. Submitted June 9, 1925 Decided October 5, 1925.

Before Justices Trencard, Katkenbach and Lloyd.

Eor the prosecutors, Bcammell & Besore. For the defendant, Edward L. Kalzenbach. Pee Curiam.

After a full examination of this case we have reached the conclusion that the judgment of the Prerogative Court should be affirmed, for the reasons expressed in the opinion delivered by Vice Chancellor-Buchanan, and reported in 2 N. J. Adv. R. 843.
